The White House Press Secretary announced that President Obama will attend the 17th Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) leaders' meeting in Singapore. The President will work with APEC leaders to promote open trade and investment, support economic recovery and sustainable development, and address key challenges facing the region and the world. The President is also expected to visit other countries during his trip to the region, although specific details have not been finalized. In addition, the Press Secretary provided updates on the President's activities regarding healthcare reform, including town hall meetings and discussions with lawmakers. The Press Secretary also addressed questions about the President's support for a public option, the PhRMA deal, and Guantanamo Bay.